    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-06-28T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-06-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="91"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d91">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.0141 Phoenix Group/95¾</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by President <persName type="from"
                            >Roosevelt</persName> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Hyde Park, N. Y.</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-06-28">June 28,
                            1938</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>I think this proposed answer to the British<note n="90" xml:id="d91fn90">
                        <hi rend="italic">Infra.</hi>
                    </note> is all right—but Joe Kennedy tells me he has made one or two
                    suggestions.</p>
                <p>Will you please discuss with the Interior Department the possibility of our
                    moving half a dozen families to Canton Island from the Hawaiian Islands or
                    Samoa. If the British can do a little colonizing why can’t we also?</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>F[<hi rend="smallcaps">ranklin</hi>] D. R[<hi rend="smallcaps"
                            >oosevelt</hi>]</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
